brainly_data.question: Which behavior is a sign that someone is having a heart attack? The person complains of chest pain and has difficulty breathing. The person clutches his or her throat and coughs. The person has a seizure.
brainly_data.subject: Health

all_answers.question: Which behavior is a sign that someone is having a heart attack? The person complains of chest pain and has difficulty breathing. The person clutches his or her throat and coughs. The person has a seizure.
all_answers.subject: Health
all_answers.text:
Males will have chest pain, difficulty breathing, numbness or tingling in the left arm/side.

women might have the same with pain in the back/lower back.
